[The WNV case numbers are increasing in Europe at a faster rate this year [2018], owing to an earlier rise in vector activity because of warmer temperatures; the presence of a working surveillance system has been able to detect and document this, which can help public health officials plan control measures accordingly. - Mod.UBA

References to the reports in Eurosurveillance are as follows:
1. Riccardo F, Monaco F, Bella A, Savini G, Russo F, Cagarelli R, et al. An early start of West Nile virus seasonal transmission: the added value of One Heath surveillance in detecting early circulation and triggering timely response in Italy, June to July 2018. Euro Surveill. 2018;23(32):pii=1800427. https://doi.org/10.2807/1560-7917.ES.2018.23.32.1800427.
2. Haussig J M, Young J J, Gossner C M, Mezei E, Bella A, Sirbu A, et al. Early start of the West Nile fever transmission season 2018 in Europe. Euro Surveill. 2018;23(32):pii=1800428. https://doi.org/10.2807/1560-7917.ES.2018.23.32.1800428.
- Mod.SH

